{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771594928,"nonce":"Prq221KgYgapPvEIBw33pqsaVg8=","title":"Searchkick::InvalidQueryError not rescued in search_people","message":"When Elasticsearch is reachable but has a stale index (e.g. fullname mapped as text instead of keyword), search_people throws Searchkick::InvalidQueryError which is not caught by the rescue block. This causes 500 errors in checkout, borrowers, and lending controllers.\n\nThe rescue currently catches Faraday::ConnectionFailed, Errno::ECONNREFUSED, and Elastic::Transport::Transport::Error but not Searchkick::InvalidQueryError.\n\nFix: add Searchkick::InvalidQueryError to the rescue clause in Borrower.search_people.","files":null}]}